# Line-ending policy.
#
# These file types are EXECUTED on the Linux VPS. If they are ever
# committed with CRLF (e.g. a contributor/agent on Windows without
# core.autocrlf=true), bash fails with `bad interpreter: ...^M` and
# systemd rejects the unit — a silent break of the disk janitor that
# prevents the 2026-05-17 outage. Force LF in the repo regardless of
# the committing machine's git config so this whole class of
# "works here, breaks on the VPS" bug is impossible.
*.sh        text eol=lf
*.bash      text eol=lf
*.service   text eol=lf
*.timer     text eol=lf
*.mjs       text eol=lf
Justfile    text eol=lf

# Binary data files: never text-normalize. stars.bin (HOSSTAR1 star
# catalog, generated by scripts/build-stars-bin.js) contains raw f32/u16
# records; a CRLF rewrite would corrupt every record after the first
# 0x0A byte. Git auto-detects binaries today, but pin it so no future
# `* text=auto` rule can ever mangle it.
*.bin       binary
